-- ScyllaDB FTS demo -- vector (semantic) search, runnable in cqlsh.
--
-- Semantic search is a SEPARATE ANN query (not hybrid with BM25). It runs against
-- the SAME chat.messages table, ordering by the `embedding` column instead of a
-- BM25 clause. The query vector below is the all-MiniLM-L6-v2 (384-dim) embedding
-- of the natural-language query in the comment; it is precomputed and inlined so
-- cqlsh needs no embedding model at runtime.
--
-- Apply after 01_keyspace, 02_tables, vector/03_index_vector, 04_seed_data, and
-- wait for the vector index (messages_vec_ann) to report SERVING.

USE chat;

-- Semantic query: "planning a trip overseas for the summer".
-- Lexically this shares NO words with the target message, yet ANN returns
-- "let's book flights to Bali and spend two weeks on the beach..." at the top --
-- semantic proximity, not keyword overlap.

